  <h2 id="reading-resources">Reading Resources for Every Level</h2>
  <p>Reading builds vocabulary passively and reinforces grammar patterns. Start with material slightly below your level (understand 90%+ of words) and gradually increase difficulty:</p>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
    <div style="background: #f0fdf4; border: 2px solid #22c55e; padding: 1.2rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #16a34a;">🌱 Beginner Reading</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li><strong>Tadoku Graded Readers</strong> — free online, levels 0–5</li>
        <li><strong>NHK Easy News</strong> — simplified articles with furigana</li>
        <li><strong>Satori Reader</strong> — stories with grammar notes (some free)</li>
        <li><strong>Children's books</strong> — simple language with illustrations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div style="background: #eff6ff; border: 2px solid #3b82f6; padding: 1.2rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #2563eb;">📘 Intermediate Reading</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li><strong>Manga</strong> — natural dialogue with visual context</li>
        <li><strong>Light novels</strong> — often with furigana on kanji</li>
        <li><strong>NHK regular news</strong> — standard Japanese reporting</li>
        <li><strong>Wikipedia Japanese</strong> — familiar topics in Japanese</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div style="background: #fdf2f8; border: 2px solid #ec4899; padding: 1.2rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #db2777;">🎯 Advanced Reading</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li><strong>Novels</strong> — Murakami, Yoshimoto, contemporary fiction</li>
        <li><strong>News sites</strong> — 朝日新聞, 読売新聞, NHK</li>
        <li><strong>2ch / 5ch</strong> — internet forums (colloquial Japanese)</li>
        <li><strong>Academic papers</strong> — for specialized vocabulary</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="speaking-practice">Speaking and Pronunciation Practice</h2>
